FROM Chapter 15 Polymorphism and Virtual Functions
13th February 2017 Tuesday
--------------------------------------------------

Program 15-8 Encryption Framework

There's this code: virtual ... final.

Here's the answer:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/44153281/does-it-make-sense-to-add-final-keyword-to-the-virtual-function-in-a-class-that?noredirect=1&lq=1

	"
	If you don't mark the function as virtual and final then the child-class can still implement the function and hide the base-class function.

	By making the function virtual and final the child-class can not override or hide the function.
	"
